                              = Entry to compos =

     ù The entry fee for all the competitions is the disk your work is on.
     ù If we find any kind of virus on any entry, then ALL the entries of
       the competitor will be disqualified.
     ù Everything you compete with has to be copied onto the compomachine.
       An organizer will be available along with the compomachine. At this
       time you can check that your work has been successfully transfered
       to our machine. (Intros and demos can be ran right away.) We will
       need the disks though (ie. in case of virii). If the disk contains
       entries to several compos (ie. a 64k intro and some graphics), then
       be sure to tell the organizer who copied your work, so that your
       entry won't be lost this way.
     ù Competitors on the PC should give us their work on 3.5" HD disks,
       and those competing on the Amiga should give us their work on 3.5"
       DD disks. This is very important for the organizing.
     ù Every disk should contain every important info related to the entry
       like : TITLE/AUTHOR/GROUP/COMPO.
     ù Every production MUST have a FILE_ID.DIZ, which should contain the
       following:
               - Title of the production,
               - Name of the competitor,
               - Name of the group,
               - Which compo the production will compete in,
               - Which party the production was released on.
     ù If there is some important information about the entry that we should
       know, then write it in a file called FONTOS.!!! .



                              = JuRy aNd vOtInG =

     ù The preselection jury will be made up of the members of the teams
       that are organizing the party, furthermore people can apply in
       restricted numbers. (Maximum 10 jurymembers.)
     ù Only people who do not compete in the respective compo can be
       jury members for that competition.
     ù Jury members will rate the competing works on a scale of 1 to 10,
       the works with highest points will compete in the compos.
     . The number of competitors varies from competition to competition.
     . Those works that get through to the compos will be voted on with
       a system of 5 - 3 - 1 points depending on which place the audience
       puts them.



